I can't read it from this side.
Ah, what's up~ It's Hikaru. I was surprised.
Hey hey, have you seen the rabbit?
No no~ Not accessories or anything, a real rabbit.
I'm sure I saw it somewhere around here...
Why suddenly a rabbit? Are you trying to raise it?
Huh? What are you talking about?
Well obviously, I'm going to eat it.

Kanae confidently declares their wildness with their usual
bright expression.
It feels like the genre suddenly drifted in survival.
No, strictly speaking, it's not the wrong word but...

By the way, this area is a sulfur zone, so it seems
dangerous.
Oh, how did you know? The smell?
No, it was written on the signboard.
Ehh~ Come on! Right now, I want to eat meat!

Of course, it goes without saying, but the meat that I
brought was already completely eaten on the first day.

It's not strange for her, a super carnivorous girl, to
develop a forbidden meat craving...

Hehe~ That's nice. If I bring meat, I'll do something
special for Hikaru.
What do you mean by something special?

Oh~ That's just something to look forward to at that time,
right?
No, I don't know what it is...
Anyway, bring it! I'll also search around for it.

Since they say it's dangerous here... Maybe I should try
looking somewhere else... Hehe~
Oh~ I'm looking for meat~ The grass is... no good~
And Kanae left while singing a strange song.
Should I try looking for it, just in case?
